==Old English==

===Etymology===
Germanic ''frî-'' ‘to [[love]]’.
There are cognates in Old Frisian [[fretho]], Old Saxon [[frithu]] (Dutch [[vrede]]), Old High German [[fridu]] (German [[Friede]]), Old Norse [[friðr]] (Swedish and Danish [[fred]]).
